  <p>
    Most septic failures are slow, preventable, and expensive — in that order. The good news is that
    preventing them doesn't take special knowledge or much effort, just a few habits done
    consistently. This checklist lays them out and, just as importantly, explains why each matters, so
    it becomes a routine that sticks rather than a list you read once and forget. For the deeper
    background on any item, our full <a href="/septic-maintenance/">septic maintenance guide</a> goes
    further.
  </p>

